org.dexpi.pid.imaging.drawableElements

Class CircleElement

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.dexpi.pid.imaging.drawableElements.DrawableElement
      • org.dexpi.pid.imaging.drawableElements.CircleElement

  • public class CircleElement
extends DrawableElement
    The circle element. Describes the outline of a circular arc. The resulting arc begins at startAngle and ends at endAngle degrees, using the color. Angles are interpreted such that 0 degrees is at the 3 o'clock position and the angle increases counter-clockwise.
    Author:
    El Pulpo

      • CircleElement

        public CircleElement(java.awt.Color color,
                     float lineWeight,
                     double[] position,
                     double radius,
                     double startAngle,
                     double endAngle,
                     boolean filled)
        Creates a new circle element. If only a portion of the circle should be drawn, use start angle and end angle. The angle is measured counter clockwise, starting at 3 o'clock.
        Parameters:
        color - the color
        lineWeight - the line weight
        position - the position of the midpoint
        radius - the radius
        startAngle - the start angle ( in degrees)
        endAngle - the end angle (in degrees)
        filled - filled
